 the Lewinsky scandal, it is easy to overlook the president’s humble upbringing, as well as his many achievements at home and abroad: the longest economic boom in American history, a balanced budget, successful intervention in the Balkans, and a series of landmark, if controversial, free-trade agreements. Through the candid recollections of Takiff’s many subjects, A Complicated Man leaves no area unexplored, revealing the most complete and unexpected portrait of our forty-second president published to date.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEntretiensxÉtats-Unis. 0aEx-presidentsxBiographyxUnited States. 0aEx-presidentszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aEx-présidentsxBiographiesxÉtats-Unis. 0aGouverneursxBiographiesxArkansas. 0aGovernorsxBiographyxArkansas. 0aGovernorszArkansasvBiography. 0aInterviewsxUnited States. 0aInterviewszUnited States. 0aPresidentsxBiographyxUnited States. 0aPresidentszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aPrésidentsxBiographiesxÉtats-Unis. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Presidents & Heads of State.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030016888440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300168884423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300168884/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles